import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['age'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(gender_counts.index, title="Gender", loc="best")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    race_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red', 'cyan', 'magenta', 'yellow', 'black'])
    plt.title('What is the racial distribution of the deceased individuals?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Race')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Deceased Individuals')
    plt.legend(race_counts.index, title='Races')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from shapely.geometry import Point

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Create a GeoDataFrame from the DataFrame
    geometry = [Point(xy) for xy in zip(data['longitude'], data['latitude'])]
    gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(data, geometry=geometry)

    # Create a base map
    world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    base = world.boundary.plot(color='black', linewidth=1, figsize=(10, 6))

    # Plot the death locations on the map
    gdf.plot(ax=base, marker='o', color='red', markersize=5, legend=True)

    # Set the title
    plt.title('What is the distribution of death locations?', wrap=True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
